item.content:encoded:
The Magento API supports SOAP and XML-RPC, where SOAP is the default protocol. In this article we will cover a practical example of using SOAP API.

One of the nice features of Magento API is that it allows you to add images to product, not just one, two or three images like you get via CSV import, but entire gallery of images. Now, the speed at which you can do this is a whole new topic, one that would not like to get to deep into. All you need to know is that Magento SOAP API is all but fast, remember that when working on large scales.<!--more-->

SOAP API in Magento comes in <strong><em>three flavors</em></strong>:
<ul>
	<li>SOAP API <em>v1</em></li>
	<li>SOAP API <em>v2</em></li>
	<li>SOAP API <em>v2</em> WS-I mode
(WSDL for the SOAP v2 API is different when in WS-I compliant mode)</li>
</ul>
If this is the first time you are hearing about SOAP, WSDL  and WS-I terminology, I encourage you to do a bit of Google search on those terms.

Additionally, if you are not just consuming Magento API, but need a deeper understanding of its inner workings, I suggest you take a look at these excellent articles by Alan Storm:
<ul>
	<li><a href="http://alanstorm.com/magento_soap_api_shell_scripts">Scrubbing Bubbles for Magento's SOAP</a></li>
	<li><a href="http://alanstorm.com/magento_api_tutorial">The Magento API</a></li>
	<li><a href="http://alanstorm.com/magento_api_adapater_xml_rpc">Magento API Adapters and Handlers</a></li>
	<li><a href="http://alanstorm.com/magento_api_soap_adapaters_and_handlers">Magento API SOAP Adapaters and Handlers</a></li>
	<li><a href="http://alanstorm.com/debugging_magento_api_method_calls">Debugging Magento API Method Calls</a></li>
	<li><a href="http://alanstorm.com/magento_soap_v2_adapter">Magento's SOAP V2 Adapater</a></li>
	<li><a href="http://alanstorm.com/magentos_wsi_compliant_api">Magento's WS-I Compliant API</a></li>
</ul>
Now lets get down to some practical examples. What follows are three examples that do the same thing, each one for specific flavor of SOAP API. In order to understand the examples and have them working you will need to have php_soap and php_fileinfo extensions installed on your server.

<strong>Request Example SOAP V1</strong>
<pre><code class="language-php"><?php

/**
 * Resource:catalog_product_attribute_media
 * http://www.magentocommerce.com/api/soap/catalog/catalogProductAttributeMedia/catalog_product_attribute_media.create.html
 */

ini_set('display_errors', 1);

$imgFolder = 'C:/Users/Ajzele/Desktop/TEMP2/';
$productId = 166;
$shop = 'http://magento-ce-17.foggyline.net/';
$apiUser = 'foggyline';
$apiKey = 'api123';

$images = array(
    array(
        'name' => 'Sample Img1',
        'content' => base64_encode(file_get_contents($imgFolder.'sample1.jpg')),
        'mime' => finfo_file(finfo_open(FILEINFO_MIME_TYPE), $imgFolder.'sample1.jpg')
    ),
    array(
        'name' => 'Sample Img2',
        'content' => base64_encode(file_get_contents($imgFolder.'sample2.jpg')),
        'mime' => finfo_file(finfo_open(FILEINFO_MIME_TYPE), $imgFolder.'sample2.jpg')
    ),
    array(
        'name' => 'Sample Img3',
        'content' => base64_encode(file_get_contents($imgFolder.'sample3.jpeg')),
        'mime' => finfo_file(finfo_open(FILEINFO_MIME_TYPE), $imgFolder.'sample3.jpeg')
    ),
    array(
        'name' => 'Sample Img4',
        'content' => base64_encode(file_get_contents($imgFolder.'sample4.jpg')),
        'mime' => finfo_file(finfo_open(FILEINFO_MIME_TYPE), $imgFolder.'sample4.jpg')
    ),
    array(
        'name' => 'Sample Img5',
        'content' => base64_encode(file_get_contents($imgFolder.'sample5.gif')),
        'mime' => finfo_file(finfo_open(FILEINFO_MIME_TYPE), $imgFolder.'sample5.gif')
    ),
    array(
        'name' => 'Sample Img6',
        'content' => base64_encode(file_get_contents($imgFolder.'sample6.png')),
        'mime' => finfo_file(finfo_open(FILEINFO_MIME_TYPE), $imgFolder.'sample6.png')
    ),   
);

/* START Request Example SOAP V1 */
$proxy = new SoapClient($shop.'api/soap/?wsdl');
$session = $proxy->login($apiUser, $apiKey);

foreach ($images as $image) {

    $result = $proxy->call(
            $session,
            'catalog_product_attribute_media.create',
            array(
                    $productId,
                    array('file'=>$image, 'label'=>$image['name'], 'position'=>'1', 'types'=>array('thumbnail'), 'exclude'=>0)
            )
    );
}

exit('END Request Example SOAP V1');
/* END Request Example SOAP V1 */</code></pre>

