Depending on your Magento Indexer <em>Mode</em> settings (Manual Update / Update on Save) you might have the "One or more of the Cache Types are invalidated: Blocks HTML output. Click here to go to Cache Management and refresh cache types." notification message popping out all the time in Magento admin.

This message is basically telling you that you need to go under "System > Cache Management" and refresh the invalidated cache types manually. Until you do so, Magento considers the invalidated cache types as disabled. If you have a high traffic store where every second of page generation / page load time counts, then this is an issue. You need to refresh the invalidated cache types as soon as possible. Doing so manually is simply not an viable option, since it takes time and constant monitoring.<!--more-->

To bypass this, here is a little code snippet that does the job of programmatically refreshing invalidated cache types. Just put int your own PHP script that you can trigger via system cron every few minutes or so. The script checks only for invalidated cache types, so it should not impose itself as resource intensive.

<pre><code class="language-php">
$_invalidatedCacheTypes = Mage::app()->getCacheInstance()->getInvalidatedTypes();

$invalidatedCacheTypes = array();

foreach ($_invalidatedCacheTypes as $invalidatedCacheType) {
	$invalidatedCacheTypes[] = $invalidatedCacheType->getId();
}

foreach (Mage::app()->getCacheInstance()->getTypes() as $type) {
	if (in_array($type->getId(), $invalidatedCacheTypes)) {
		Mage::app()->getCacheInstance()->cleanType($type);
	}
}  
</code></pre>

Hope this helps.

