However, the examples in this article are intentionally a bit more low level, as they are done in PHP cURL.

<h3>The <em>Access Token</em></h3>

The first thing we need to do is to make a <em>/token</em> call using our application's OAuth keys (Client ID, Secret). Following code is an example of how we do it in PHP cURL.

<pre><code class="language-php">define('CLIENT_ID', 'Ab0n2BDk4pHXLwu0UA4Zy5z6B0Ro6XmZFdupTbXjTGjqk_jv9vu80awY9IdU');
define('CLIENT_SECRET', 'EHxEvBDwNgxy8TKeCaaVeJKvckXGTBBeGijk8xVn5SBelx3YaMEmI4PJZM8V');

$ch = curl_init();

$options = array(
	CURLOPT_URL => 'https://api.sandbox.paypal.com/v1/oauth2/token',
	CURLOPT_POST => 1,
	CURLOPT_POSTFIELDS => 'grant_type=client_credentials',
	CURLOPT_RETURNTRANSFER => 1,
	CURLOPT_HTTPHEADER => array('Accept: application/json'),
	CURLOPT_SSL_VERIFYPEER => false, /* security issue... OK for testing :P */
	CURLOPT_USERPWD => CLIENT_ID.':'.CLIENT_SECRET,
);

curl_setopt_array($ch, $options);

$response = curl_exec($ch);
$curl_errno = curl_errno($ch);
$curl_error = curl_error($ch);
curl_close($ch);

if ($curl_errno > 0) {
	echo sprintf('cURL Error #%s : %s.', $curl_errno, $curl_error);
} else {
	$obj = json_decode($response);

	$access_token = (isset($obj->access_token)) ? $obj->access_token : false;

	if ($access_token) {
		//Save $access_token for further API calls
	}
}</code></pre>

If all goes well, the value of $response variable should contain something like following:

<pre><code class="language-php">/*
stdClass Object
(
	[scope] => openid https://uri.paypal.com/services/invoicing https://api.paypal.com/v1/payments/.* https://api.paypal.com/v1/vault/credit-card/.* https://api.paypal.com/v1/vault/credit-card
	[access_token] => g3J6FmsSvIbtx0vhX7wKA53zBL4GVod2Xf9t4za84qA
	[token_type] => Bearer
	[app_id] => APP-80W284485P519543T
	[expires_in] => 28800
)	
*/</code></pre>

As you can see, access_token is contained within the response body.

<h3><i>Store</i> a credit card</h3>

Once we have access token we can make /credit-card call like shown below.

<pre><code class="language-php">if ($access_token) {

	$cardInfo = array(
		'payer_id' => 'GI6WdoVY6zOq'.time(),
		'type' => 'visa',
		'number' => '4417119669820331',
